{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/blog/2016/css4-selectors","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>A CSS selector is like patterns which are used to select and style the pattern matching elements. We will compare <code class=\"language-text\">CSS3</code> with <code class=\"language-text\">CSS4</code> selectors and give some examples for better understanding.</p>\n<h2>Pseudo Class</h2>\n<p>Pseudo class in CSS is used to defined a special state of an element. Such as visited links have the state of <code class=\"language-text\">:visited</code>.</p>\n<h2>CSS3</h2>\n<h3>:not()</h3>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">:not</code> pseudo class selector is used to select all the elements except the one which is specified in the argument.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"html\"><pre class=\"language-html\"><code class=\"language-html\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>a</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">href</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>/<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">class</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>link<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Link 1<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>a</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>a</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">href</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>No Link<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>a</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>a</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">href</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">rel</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>nofollow<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>No Follow<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>a</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>a</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">href</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>/<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">class</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>link<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Link 2<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>a</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></code></pre></div>\n<p>We have 4 <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;a&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</code> tags, two with a class <code class=\"language-text\">link</code> and one with <code class=\"language-text\">rel</code> attribute and one normal link.</p>\n<p>So lets set the color of all the anchor tags to <span class=\"color__red\"><code class=\"language-text\">red</code></span> expect the one’s which has class <code class=\"language-text\">.link</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">a:not(.link)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">color</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> red<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Example:</h3>\n<p data-height=\"265\" data-theme-id=\"dark\" data-slug-hash=\"NdmWWz\" data-default-tab=\"html,result\" data-user=\"gokulkrishh\" data-embed-version=\"2\" data-pen-title=\"CSS3 :not selector\" class=\"codepen\">See the Pen <a href=\"http://codepen.io/gokulkrishh/pen/NdmWWz/\">CSS3 :not selector</a> by Gokulakrishnan Kalaikovan (<a href=\"http://codepen.io/gokulkrishh\">@gokulkrishh</a>) on <a href=\"http://codepen.io\">CodePen</a>.</p>\n<p>In above example, I don’t want to set the color to <span class=\"color__red\"><code class=\"language-text\">red</code></span> for <code class=\"language-text\">rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;</code>. But <code class=\"language-text\">CSS3</code> :not() selector allows only one argument.</p>\n<p>Now let us see in <b>CSS4</b>.</p>\n<h2>CSS4</h2>\n<h3>:not()</h3>\n<p>Allows setting multiple arguments for the <code class=\"language-text\">:not(selector1, selector2)</code> pseudo class selector.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">a:not(.link, [rel=\"nofollow\"])</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">color</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> red<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>The above example will let me to set the color of <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;a&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</code> tags to <span class=\"color__red\"><code class=\"language-text\">red</code></span> which doesn’t have <code class=\"language-text\">.link</code> class and <code class=\"language-text\">rel=nofollow</code> attribute.</p>\n<h3>:matches()</h3>\n<p>Takes multiple arguments and represents an element which is specified in the argument.</p>\n<p>Example:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"html\"><pre class=\"language-html\"><code class=\"language-html\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>header</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Header Title<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>header</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>General Title<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">class</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>container<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Container Title<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>section</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Section Title<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>section</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Now I want to change the color of some <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;h1&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;</code> tags to <span class=\"color__green\"><code class=\"language-text\">green</code></span>. Normally we write it likes.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">&lt;!-- Normal Way -->\nheader h1, .container h1</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">color</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> green<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token selector\">&lt;!-- CSS4 -->\n:matches(header, .container) h1</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">color</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> green<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>List of some CSS4 selectors.</h3>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Selectors</th>\n<th align=\"left\">Does</th>\n<th align=\"right\">CSS</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors4/#negation\">:not(s1, s2, s3)</a></td>\n<td align=\"left\">Allows multiple arguments</td>\n<td align=\"right\">3/4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors4/#matches\">:match(s1, s2)</a></td>\n<td align=\"left\">Matches the elements specified in the arugment</td>\n<td align=\"right\">4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors4/#attribute-case\">a[href=home i]</a></td>\n<td align=\"left\">Case Insensitive (home, HOME, Home etc,.)</td>\n<td align=\"right\">4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors4/#any-link-pseudo\">:any-link</a></td>\n<td align=\"left\">Matches source of hyperlink (a, link etc,.)</td>\n<td align=\"right\">4</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3>Browser Support:</h3>\n<p>Only <code class=\"language-text\">38%</code> of CSS4 selectors are supported by the browsers.</p>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 69.5945945945946%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"CSS4 Support\" title=\"CSS4 Support\" src=\"/static/639bc2ab690d41ba514de366856a3abc/fcda8/css4-support.png\" srcset=\"/static/639bc2ab690d41ba514de366856a3abc/12f09/css4-support.png 148w,\n/static/639bc2ab690d41ba514de366856a3abc/e4a3f/css4-support.png 295w,\n/static/639bc2ab690d41ba514de366856a3abc/fcda8/css4-support.png 590w,\n/static/639bc2ab690d41ba514de366856a3abc/efc66/css4-support.png 885w,\n/static/639bc2ab690d41ba514de366856a3abc/c83ae/css4-support.png 1180w,\n/static/639bc2ab690d41ba514de366856a3abc/d8d63/css4-support.png 2026w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n<center><i>Source <a href=\"http://css4-selectors.com/browser-selector-test/\" target=\"_blank\">Browser Selector Test</a></i></center>\n<h3>Conclusion</h3>\n<p>There are close to 22 new CSS level 4 selectors. Some of them are really cool and let us write less CSS code. But like mentioned above not all the browsers supports the level 4 selectors. Thanks for reading and see you in my next blog post. If you like my post, share it or comment below.</p>\n<h4>Articles</h4>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors4\" target=\"_blank\">Full list of CSS4 selectors</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://css4.rocks/\" target=\"_blank\">CSS4 Rocks</a></li>\n</ul>\n<script async src=\"https://production-assets.codepen.io/assets/embed/ei.js\"></script>\n<p> Thanks for reading my blog post 😁</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"February 28, 2016","path":"/blog/2016/css4-selectors","title":"CSS4 Selectors","readtime":null,"description":null}}},"pageContext":{}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}